07/10/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A two-day meeting of the Black Sea Economic Co-operation Organisation's (BSECO) working group for combating crime opened Monday (6 October) in Bucharest.
The session is aimed at drafting a protocol to bolster co-operation in the fight against global terrorism.
BSECO includes Albania, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Bulgaria, Georgia, Greece, Moldova, Russia, Romania, Turkey and Ukraine.
In other news, a new poll released Monday suggests Prime Minister Adrian Nastase, President Ion Iliescu and Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana enjoy the highest public approval ratings in Romania.
The survey was conducted by the IMAS Institute earlier this month.
(ACT Media - 07/10/03;
Rompres - 06/10/03)
